<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Scruggs</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-21"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 21,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 88.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 100 of the 3d
                        instant, inclosing a map showing the British claims to the territory in
                        dispute between the Governments of Great Britain and Venezuela. Copies of
                        your dispatch and of its inclosure have been transmitted to our minister at
                        London.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>